        <briefdescription>
<para>This API Validates the tag parameters for the specified AES engine mode. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>EngineMode</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>AES engine mode. </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>TagAddr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Address of the Input/Output Tag buffer. </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>TagLen</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Length of the tag in bytes. It will be zero for all AES standard modes like, ECB, CBC, OFB, CFB, CTR</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>XST_SUCCESS, if the tag parameters are successfully validated.</para></listitem><listitem><para>XST_FAILURE, if the tag parameters validation fails. </para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
<para>Tag Validation for respective AES engine modes AES Standard mode (ECB, CBC, CTR, CFB, OFB). AES MAC mode (GCM, CCM, GMAC, CMAC).</para><para><table rows="4" cols="3"><row>
<entry thead="yes"><para>Engine Mode </para></entry><entry thead="yes"><para>TagAddress </para></entry><entry thead="yes"><para>TagLength  </para></entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para>Standard mode </para></entry><entry thead="no"><para>N/A </para></entry><entry thead="no"><para>N/A </para></entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para>AES-GCM, CMAC </para></entry><entry thead="no"><para>Non-zero </para></entry><entry thead="no"><para>8&lt;=TagLen&lt;=16 </para></entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para>AES-CCM </para></entry><entry thead="no"><para>Non-zero </para></entry><entry thead="no"><para>4,6,8,10,12,14,16 </para></entry></row>
</table>
NIST recommends using a tag length of at least 64 bits to provide adequate protection against guessing attacks.</para>        </inbodydescription>
